DaemonSets in Kubernetes — One Pod Per Node

 Key Properties:

• Ensures exactly one Pod runs on every node (or selected nodes using nodeSelector/affinity)

• Automatically creates a new Pod when a node joins the cluster

• Automatically removes Pods when nodes leave the cluster

• Perfect for cluster-wide agents and daemons that must run everywhere

 DaemonSet vs Deployment

✅ Deployment
• You control replica count
• Pods can run on any node

✅ DaemonSet
• Kubernetes ensures one Pod per node
• No replica count needed

📌 Common Use Cases:

• Log collectors (Fluentd)
• Monitoring agents (Node Exporter)
• Security agents
• CNI networking plugins
